15;margin-top:0px"><code style=3D"font-family:&quot;Google Sans Text&quot;,=
sans-serif;line-height:1.15;margin-top:0px">SparkConnectService</code></b> =
to return resolved schemas of relations during standard plan execution.</p>=
</li><li style=3D"line-height:1.15;margin-top:0px"><p style=3D"line-height:=
1.15;margin-top:0px"><b style=3D"line-height:1.15;margin-top:0px">Local Sch=
ema Cache:</b> A configurable client-side cache in the <b style=3D"line-hei=
ght:1.15;margin-top:0px"><code style=3D"font-family:&quot;Google Sans Text&=
quot;,sans-serif;line-height:1.15;margin-top:0px">SparkSession</code></b> t=
o store resolved schemas.</p></li><li style=3D"line-height:1.15;margin-top:=
0px"><p style=3D"line-height:1.15;margin-top:0px"><b style=3D"line-height:1=
.15;margin-top:0px">Batched Analysis API:</b> An extension to the <b style=
=3D"line-height:1.15;margin-top:0px"><code style=3D"font-family:&quot;Googl=
e Sans Text&quot;,sans-serif;line-height:1.15;margin-top:0px">AnalyzePlan</=
code></b> protocol to allow schema resolution for multiple DataFrames in a =
single batch call.</p></li></ol><p style=3D"font-family:&quot;Google Sans T=
ext&quot;,sans-serif;line-height:1.15;margin-top:0px">This shift would ensu=
re that Spark Connect provides the same &quot;fluid&quot; interactive exper=
ience as Spark Classic, removing the <span style=3D"line-height:1.15;margin=
-top:0px">$O(N)$</span> network latency overhead for metadata-heavy operati=
ons .</p><p style=3D"font-family:&quot;Google Sans Text&quot;,sans-serif;li=
ne-height:1.15;margin-top:0px">I have drafted a full SPIP document ready fo=
r review=C2=A0 , which includes the proposed changes for the <b style=3D"li=
ne-height:1.15;margin-top:0px"><code style=3D"font-family:&quot;Google Sans=
 Text&quot;,sans-serif;line-height:1.15;margin-top:0px">SparkConnectService=
</code></b> and <b style=3D"line-height:1.15;margin-top:0px"><code style=3D=
"font-family:&quot;Google Sans Text&quot;,sans-serif;line-height:1.15;margi=
n-top:0px">AnalyzePlan</code></b> handlers.</p><p style=3D"font-family:&quo=
