It=E2=80=99s time to send our ASF report again this Wednesday. Let me =
know if you want to change anything in this. Here=E2=80=99s my draft:

=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D

Description:

Apache Spark is a fast and general purpose engine for large-scale data =
processing. It offers high-level APIs in Java, Scala, Python, R and SQL =
as well as a rich set of libraries including stream processing, machine =
learning, and graph analytics.

Issues for the board:

- None

Project Status:

- Released Apache Spark 4.0.2 on Feb 5, 2026.
- Released Apache Spark 3.5.8 on Jan 23, 2026.
- Released Apache Spark 4.2.0 preview1 on Jan 11, 2026.
- Released Apache Spark 4.1.1 on Jan 9, 2026.
- Released Apache Spark 4.1.0 on Dec 16, 2025.
- Released Apache Spark Connect Swift Client 0.5.0 on Jan 15, 2026.
- Released Apache Spark K8S Operator 0.7.0 on Jan 15, 2026.
- Recently Accepted SPIPs:
    1. Improving Spark SQL UDFs with Transpilation
    2. Accelerating Apache Spark Release Cadence
    3. The metrics & semantic modeling in Spark
- Release Process Update
    - The vote to stop preview releases after Spark 4.2 has been =
accepted.

Trademarks:

- No changes since last report.

Latest releases:

- Spark 4.0.2 was released on Feb 5, 2026
- Spark 3.5.8 was released on Jan 23, 2026
- Spark 4.1.1 was released on Jan 9, 2026

Committers and PMC:

- The latest committer was added on July 1, 2025 (Anton Okolnychyi).
- The latest PMC member was added on Jan 21st, 2025 (Jie Yang).

