s=3D"gmail_quote" style=3D"margin:0px 0px 0px 0.8ex;border-left:1px solid r=
gb(204,204,204);padding-left:1ex"><div dir=3D"ltr"><p>Hi Wenchen,</p>
<p>Great question. In the SPIP, the language runtime is carried in the func=
tion spec (for <code style=3D"font-family:monospace">python</code> / <code =
style=3D"font-family:monospace">python-pandas</code>) so catalogs can optio=
nally declare constraints on the execution environment.</p>
<p>Concretely, the spec can include optional fields like:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code style=3D"font-family:monospace">pythonVersion</code> (e.g., <code =
style=3D"font-family:monospace">&quot;3.10&quot;</code>)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><code style=3D"font-family:monospace">requirements</code> (pip-style spe=
cs)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><code style=3D"font-family:monospace">environmentUri</code> (optional po=
inter to a pre-built / admin-approved environment)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p>For the initial stage, we assume execution uses the existing PySpark wor=
ker environment (same as regular Python UDF / pandas UDF). If <code style=
=3D"font-family:monospace">pythonVersion</code> / <code style=3D"font-famil=
y:monospace">requirements</code> are present, Spark can validate them again=
st the current worker env and fail fast (AnalysisException) if they=E2=80=
=99re not satisfied.</p>
<p><code style=3D"font-family:monospace">environmentUri</code> is intended =
as an extension point for future integration (or vendor plugins) to select =
a vetted environment, but we don=E2=80=99t assume Spark will provision envi=
ronments out-of-the-box in v1.</p><p>Thanks,</p><p>Huaxin</p></div><br><div=
 class=3D"gmail_quote"><div dir=3D"ltr" class=3D"gmail_attr">On Wed, Jan 7,=
 2026 at 6:06=E2=80=AFPM Wenchen Fan &lt;<a href=3D"mailto:cloud0fan@gmail.=
com" target=3D"_blank">cloud0fan@gmail.com</a>&gt; wrote:<br></div><blockqu=
ote class=3D"gmail_quote" style=3D"margin:0px 0px 0px 0.8ex;border-left:1px=
 solid rgb(204,204,204);padding-left:1ex"><div dir=3D"ltr">This is a great =
feature! How do we define the language runtime? e.g. the Python version and=
 libraries. Do we assume the Python runtime is the same as the PySpark work=
er?</div><br><div class=3D"gmail_quote"><div dir=3D"ltr" class=3D"gmail_att=
r">On Thu, Jan 8, 2026 at 3:12=E2=80=AFAM huaxin gao &lt;<a href=3D"mailto:=
huaxin.gao11@gmail.com" target=3D"_blank">huaxin.gao11@gmail.com</a>&gt; wr=
ote:<br></div><blockquote class=3D"gmail_quote" style=3D"margin:0px 0px 0px=
 0.8ex;border-left:1px solid rgb(204,204,204);padding-left:1ex"><div dir=3D=
"ltr"><div dir=3D"ltr"><div dir=3D"ltr"><div dir=3D"ltr"><div dir=3D"ltr"><=
p>Hi All,</p><p>I=E2=80=99d like to start a discussion on a draft <a href=
=3D"https://docs.google.com/document/d/186cTAZxoXp1p8vaSunIaJmVLXcPR-FxSiLi=
DUl8kK8A/edit?tab=3Dt.0#heading=3Dh.for1fb3tezo3" target=3D"_blank">SPIP</a=
>:</p><p><strong>SPIP: Catalog-backed Code-Literal Functions (SQL and Pytho=
n) with Catalog SPI and CRUD</strong></p><p><strong>Problem:</strong> Spark=
 can=E2=80=99t load SQL/Python function bodies from external catalogs in a =
standard way today, so users rely on session registration or vendor extensi=
ons.</p><p><strong>Proposal:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Add <code style=3D"font=
-family:monospace">CodeLiteralFunctionCatalog</code> (Java SPI) returning <=
code style=3D"font-family:monospace">CodeFunctionSpec</code> with implement=
ations (<code style=3D"font-family:monospace">spark-sql</code>, <code style=
=3D"font-family:monospace">python</code>, <code style=3D"font-family:monosp=
ace">python-pandas</code>).</p></li><li><p>Resolution:</p><ul><li><p>SQL: p=
arse + inline (deterministic =E2=87=92 foldable).</p></li><li><p>Python/pan=
das: run via existing Python UDF / pandas UDF runtime (opaque).</p></li><li=
><p>SQL TVF: parse to plan, substitute params, validate schema.</p></li></u=
l></li><li><p>DDL: <code style=3D"font-family:monospace">CREATE/REPLACE/DRO=
P FUNCTION</code> delegates to the catalog if it implements the SPI; otherw=
ise fall back.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Precedence + defaults:</strong></p><=
ul><li><p>Unqualified: temp/session &gt; built-in/DSv2 &gt; code-literal (c=
urrent catalog). Qualified names resolve only in the named catalog.</p></li=
><li><p>Defaults: feature on, SQL on, Python/pandas off; optional <code sty=
le=3D"font-family:monospace">languagePreference</code>.</p></li></ul><p>Fee=
dbacks are welcomed!</p><p>Thanks,</p><p>Huaxin</p></div>
