>>>>>>>> Hi Spark devs,
>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>> I'd like to call a vote on the SPIP*: DSV2 Enhanced Partition
>>>>>>>> Stats Filtering.*
>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>> *Summary:*
>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>> The DataSource V2 (DSV2) framework does not currently provide full
>>>>>>>> data-skipping capabilities comparable to Spark-native sources, pri=
marily
>>>>>>>> due to limitations in Catalyst expression evaluation.
>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>> This SPIP bridges that gap to achieve partition-skipping parity. T=
o
>>>>>>>> support this, Spark will push new *PartitionPredicate* objects
>>>>>>>> that encapsulate Catalyst partition filter expressions and the eva=
luation
>>>>>>>> logic, allowing data sources to skip irrelevant partitions effecti=
vely.
>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>> *Relevant Links:*
>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>    -
>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>    - *SPIP Doc:*
>>>>>>>>    https://docs.google.com/document/d/17vcw411PxSRLWoK-BiLI56UiNdo=
kLWtovF8JZUlDTOo/edit?usp=3Dsharing
>>>>>>>>    -
>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>    *Discuss Thread:*
