>>>>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>>>> *Summary:*
>>>>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>>>> The DataSource V2 (DSV2) framework does not currently provide
>>>>>>>>>>> full data-skipping capabilities comparable to Spark-native sour=
ces,
>>>>>>>>>>> primarily due to limitations in Catalyst expression evaluation.
>>>>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>>>> This SPIP bridges that gap to achieve partition-skipping parity=
.
>>>>>>>>>>> To support this, Spark will push new *PartitionPredicate*
>>>>>>>>>>> objects that encapsulate Catalyst partition filter expressions =
and the
>>>>>>>>>>> evaluation logic, allowing data sources to skip irrelevant part=
itions
>>>>>>>>>>> effectively.
