>>>>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>>>>> Hi Spark devs,
>>>>>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>>>>> I'd like to call a vote on the SPIP*: DSV2 Enhanced Partition
>>>>>>>>>>>> Stats Filtering.*
>>>>>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>>>>> *Summary:*
>>>>>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>>>>> The DataSource V2 (DSV2) framework does not currently provide
>>>>>>>>>>>> full data-skipping capabilities comparable to Spark-native sou=
rces,
>>>>>>>>>>>> primarily due to limitations in Catalyst expression evaluation=
.
>>>>>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>>>>> This SPIP bridges that gap to achieve partition-skipping
>>>>>>>>>>>> parity. To support this, Spark will push new
>>>>>>>>>>>> *PartitionPredicate* objects that encapsulate Catalyst
>>>>>>>>>>>> partition filter expressions and the evaluation logic, allowin=
g data
>>>>>>>>>>>> sources to skip irrelevant partitions effectively.
>>>>>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>>>>> *Relevant Links:*
>>>>>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>>>>>    -
>>>>>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>>>>>    - *SPIP Doc:*
>>>>>>>>>>>>    https://docs.google.com/document/d/17vcw411PxSRLWoK-BiLI56U=
iNdokLWtovF8JZUlDTOo/edit?usp=3Dsharing
>>>>>>>>>>>>    -
>>>>>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>>>>>    *Discuss Thread:*
