Hi Y'all,

We've had two rounds of discussion (an informal one
https://lists.apache.org/thread/4r6q8187b30p0ppclw0pyfjp8h8xs3rq and more
formal one https://lists.apache.org/thread/90fnr43zpvl3r2n3c7px1vypj40ht6gv)
on this proposal I think we're broadly aligned now that we've scoped it
down to Spark it's self with the clarifying message that sub-projects will
set their own release and support schedule, including Spark on K8s.

The draft SPIP is
https://docs.google.com/document/d/15fb-7DNztzpQMF1MQovK75UmpC6um7KgO8cg_X5oa1I/edit?usp=sharing
and the JIRA SPARK-55489 <https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-55489>

Since this is a Friday afternoon we'll leave the vote open a little longer,
the vote will remain open until at least Tuesday March 3rd at 5pm pacific.

Cheers,

Holden :)

