>>>>>>>>>> Hi Spark devs,
>>>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>>> I'd like to call a vote on the SPIP*: DSV2 Enhanced Partition
>>>>>>>>>> Stats Filtering.*
>>>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>>> *Summary:*
>>>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>>> The DataSource V2 (DSV2) framework does not currently provide
>>>>>>>>>> full data-skipping capabilities comparable to Spark-native sourc=
es,
>>>>>>>>>> primarily due to limitations in Catalyst expression evaluation.
>>>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>>> This SPIP bridges that gap to achieve partition-skipping parity.
>>>>>>>>>> To support this, Spark will push new *PartitionPredicate*
>>>>>>>>>> objects that encapsulate Catalyst partition filter expressions a=
nd the
>>>>>>>>>> evaluation logic, allowing data sources to skip irrelevant parti=
tions
>>>>>>>>>> effectively.
>>>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>>> *Relevant Links:*
>>>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>>>    -
>>>>>>>>>>
