>>>>>>>>>>> I'd like to call a vote on the SPIP: DSV2 Enhanced Partition St=
ats Filtering.
>>>>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>>>> Summary:
>>>>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>>>> The DataSource V2 (DSV2) framework does not currently provide f=
ull data-skipping capabilities comparable to Spark-native sources, primaril=
y due to limitations in Catalyst expression evaluation.
>>>>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>>>> This SPIP bridges that gap to achieve partition-skipping parity=
. To support this, Spark will push new PartitionPredicate objects that enca=
psulate Catalyst partition filter expressions and the evaluation logic, all=
owing data sources to skip irrelevant partitions effectively.
>>>>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>>>> Relevant Links:
>>>>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>>>> SPIP Doc: https://docs.google.com/document/d/17vcw411PxSRLWoK-B=
