In that case, it seems the README may need an update to avoid confusion.

It currently recommends the Spark Docker Official Image without clearly
indicating that the docker-library repository is only periodically
synchronized.

For reference:
https://github.com/apache/spark-docker/blob/master/README.md?plain=3D1#L61


Dongjoon Hyun <dongjoon.hyun@gmail.com> =E4=BA=8E2026=E5=B9=B42=E6=9C=8827=
