> >>>>>>>>>>> Hi Spark devs,
> >>>>>>>>>>>
> >>>>>>>>>>> I'd like to call a vote on the SPIP: DSV2 Enhanced Partition
> Stats Filtering.
> >>>>>>>>>>>
> >>>>>>>>>>> Summary:
> >>>>>>>>>>>
> >>>>>>>>>>> The DataSource V2 (DSV2) framework does not currently provide
> full data-skipping capabilities comparable to Spark-native sources,
> primarily due to limitations in Catalyst expression evaluation.
> >>>>>>>>>>>
> >>>>>>>>>>> This SPIP bridges that gap to achieve partition-skipping
> parity. To support this, Spark will push new PartitionPredicate objects
> that encapsulate Catalyst partition filter expressions and the evaluation
> logic, allowing data sources to skip irrelevant partitions effectively.
> >>>>>>>>>>>
> >>>>>>>>>>> Relevant Links:
> >>>>>>>>>>>
> >>>>>>>>>>> SPIP Doc:
> https://docs.google.com/document/d/17vcw411PxSRLWoK-BiLI56UiNdokLWtovF8JZ=
UlDTOo/edit?usp=3Dsharing
> >>>>>>>>>>>
> >>>>>>>>>>> Discuss Thread:
> https://lists.apache.org/thread/p2cwngj9bmtcbmyplds833s9lwts8bwc
> >>>>>>>>>>>
> >>>>>>>>>>> JIRA: SPARK-55596
> >>>>>>>>>>>
> >>>>>>>>>>> POC PR: PR 54459
> >>>>>>>>>>>
> >>>>>>>>>>> The vote will be open for at least 72 hours. Please vote:
> >>>>>>>>>>>
