Hi Mich,
The proposal actually covers all three categories:

   - Time-based =E2=80=94 CHANGES FROM TIMESTAMP '2026-01-01' TO TIMESTAMP =
'2026-
   02-01'


   - Token-based (SCN/LSN) =E2=80=94 CHANGES FROM VERSION '1234567' TO VERS=
ION
    '2345678' =E2=80=94 VERSION accepts strings, so connectors can interpre=
t them
   as SCN, LSN, Kafka offset, etc.


   - Format-version-based =E2=80=94 CHANGES FROM VERSION 10 TO VERSION 20

This is a Data Source V2 connector interface. The syntax is
intentionally agnostic
=E2=80=94 each connector interprets "version" and "timestamp" in its own do=
main.
Spark provides the unified syntax and post-processing; connectors provide
the domain-specific change data.

